                                                    ... lines 183 - 184
                            </td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>It's not perfect yet - but this is a lot more dependable. Nothing should have change - so
try the tests:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./bin/phpunit -c app --filter testValidationErrors</div></code></pre>
<p>And yep! We're still green.</p>
<p>But go back and make the test fail somehow - like change the assert for the header.
I want to see the response for myself. Re-run things:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./bin/phpunit -c app --filter testValidationErrors</div></code></pre>
<p>Scroll up to the dumped response. Yes - we've got the <code>Content-Type</code> header, the
<code>type</code> and <code>title</code> keys, <em>and</em> a new <code>status</code> field that the spec recommends.</p>
<p>Fix that test. Ok, now we're ready for other stuff to go wrong.</p>

    
